name: Pilidiostigma tropicum L.S.Sm.
occurrenceRemarks: Canopy tree 31m x 47.9cm dbh, tree No. 23-556. Bark red-brown, rough, not tessellated like small trees. Corolla and calyx cream, filaments to. Stigma and style pink. Petioles and twigs maroon. Voucher for CSIRO-TERN plot. Very uncommon as a canopy tree, otherwise occasional.
habitat: Notophyll rainforest on clay soil derived from metamorphics. Canopy: Flindersia bourjotiana, Cardwellia, Flindersia brayleyana, Litsea leefeana and Argyrodendron trifoiolatum. Small trees and shrubs: Medicosma, Daphnandra, Psychotria, Gossia dallachiana and Atractocarpus hirtus.
locality: Danbulla National Park, TERN plot off Mt Edith Road, Robson Creek. [17 07 07 11.7S 145 37 58.7E].
